WEBVTT

00:03.304 --> 00:05.104
¶ "Square One" ¶

00:05.106 --> 00:06.505
(upbeat music plays)

00:06.507 --> 00:08.874
Hey, guys,
you know how summer break

00:08.876 --> 00:10.709
has totally sucked so far?

00:10.711 --> 00:12.678
It's been one day, Eddie.

00:12.680 --> 00:14.713
Well,
things are about to change.

00:14.715 --> 00:16.949
Chris Rock has a new
stand-up special on HBO

00:16.951 --> 00:18.717
called "Bring the Pain."

00:18.719 --> 00:23.989
I hear it's even more amazing
than "CB4," which is impossible!

00:23.991 --> 00:25.691
But our cable got canceled

00:25.693 --> 00:28.293
when they found out Mom
subscribed under a fake name.

00:28.295 --> 00:30.029
Oh, no! They found out about
Sydney Jones?

00:30.031 --> 00:31.697
I guess we can't watch
the special, then.

00:31.699 --> 00:32.698
Bam!

00:32.700 --> 00:34.967
Or can we?

00:34.969 --> 00:37.469
HBO's doing a free preview
all weekend?

00:37.471 --> 00:39.138
My girl Alison told me about it.

00:39.140 --> 00:42.007
Evan, toss me that remote.
Let's get our minds blown.

00:42.009 --> 00:44.476
We're watching "Square One."
It's educational.

00:44.478 --> 00:45.811
But that's just regular TV!

00:45.813 --> 00:47.479
You can watch that anytime!

00:47.481 --> 00:49.648
I have my routine.

00:49.650 --> 00:51.150
Emery: You might like
this show, Eddie.

00:51.152 --> 00:53.485
It has detectives
who use math to solve crimes.

00:53.487 --> 00:56.221
Do they solve the crime
of being a super boring show?

00:56.223 --> 00:57.890
Just give me the damn remote!

00:57.892 --> 00:59.725
No! It's my time! Stop it!

00:59.727 --> 01:01.226
Use your words!

01:01.228 --> 01:02.494
(indistinct shouting)

01:02.496 --> 01:04.329
Hey, hey, hey! Break it up!

01:04.331 --> 01:06.098
What's going on? Nothing.

01:06.100 --> 01:08.534
We're just talking. (Sighs)

01:08.536 --> 01:10.869
Eddie, you shouldn't be fighting
with your brothers.

01:10.871 --> 01:12.371
It's you guys against the world.

01:12.373 --> 01:13.672
You're all each other has.

01:13.674 --> 01:15.274
Louis, your brother's
on the phone.

01:15.276 --> 01:17.843
Tell that bastard to go to hell!

01:20.681 --> 01:22.114
¶ Fresh off the boat ¶

01:22.116 --> 01:23.849
¶ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go ¶

01:23.851 --> 01:25.951
¶ If you don't know, homey,
now you know ¶

01:25.953 --> 01:27.553
¶ Fresh off the boat ¶

01:27.555 --> 01:29.588
¶ Homey, you don't know
where I come from ¶

01:29.590 --> 01:31.123
¶ But I know where I'm goin' ¶

01:31.125 --> 01:33.792
¶ I'm fresh off the boat ¶

01:35.029 --> 01:36.962
Sorry, Gene, Louis is busy...

01:38.532 --> 01:40.632
doing pottery.

01:40.634 --> 01:42.701
(sighs) I'm obviously fishing.

01:42.703 --> 01:44.303
Maybe<i> I'm</i> not bad at charades.

01:44.305 --> 01:45.971
Maybe<i> you're</i> bad at charades.

01:45.973 --> 01:49.374
Louis Huang, you just said
brothers shouldn't fight.

01:49.376 --> 01:53.212
I thought we lived in Orlando,
not a make-believe lie town.

01:53.214 --> 01:54.313
Bye, Gene.

01:55.316 --> 01:56.849
Gene is coming to visit.

01:58.385 --> 01:59.785
He says he has some big news

01:59.787 --> 02:01.420
that he wants to share
in person.

02:01.422 --> 02:03.388
Is he starting another band?

02:03.390 --> 02:06.391
The Gene Huang Ragtime Explosion
didn't work out?

02:06.393 --> 02:08.393
Wasn't that also the name
of his vacuum-cleaner company?

02:08.395 --> 02:10.729
No. That was
Gene Huang Suck City.

02:10.731 --> 02:11.797
(sighs)

02:14.568 --> 02:15.667
That's not my fault.

02:21.008 --> 02:22.407
I came to terms with that.

02:22.409 --> 02:23.909
Gene's the one
who's still holding on.

02:23.911 --> 02:25.310
He's such a little baby.

02:25.312 --> 02:27.846
I feel you, Pops.
Brothers are so annoying.

02:27.848 --> 02:30.649
Be respectful.
That's your uncle.

02:30.651 --> 02:33.752
But yes, he is super annoying.

02:38.959 --> 02:41.493
Why, because he held a job
for more than six months?

02:48.969 --> 02:51.470
Give it to me! I don't care
about your stupid show!

02:51.472 --> 02:53.772
If one of you rips my shirt,
I'll destroy you!

02:53.774 --> 02:55.541
Jessica: Hey, come on!
It's mine!

02:55.543 --> 02:57.042
Stop fighting now!

02:57.044 --> 02:58.277
Hey!

02:58.279 --> 03:00.179
But I need to watch
"Bring the Pain."

03:00.181 --> 03:02.014
It's an urban
stand-up show, Mommy,

03:02.016 --> 03:03.949
rated "R"
for inappropriate content.

03:03.951 --> 03:06.552
Alison's leaving for band camp
in two weeks.

03:06.554 --> 03:08.787
We need to cram
the entire summer into 14 days,

03:08.789 --> 03:11.123
and we want to spend them
talking about this show!

03:11.125 --> 03:13.725
Forget it. I heard about
that show on "Nightly News."

03:13.727 --> 03:15.360
It's causing race riots.

03:15.362 --> 03:18.730
I am not waking up
to a race riot in my own house.

03:19.800 --> 03:21.567
Announcer:
The story you are about to see

03:21.569 --> 03:23.535
is a fib, but it's short.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.405
The names have been made up, and
the problems are real. (Sighs)

03:26.407 --> 03:30.075
¶¶

03:30.077 --> 03:31.910
I can't believe
Gene is coming to visit.

03:31.912 --> 03:34.213
We haven't seen him
since we went back to Taiwan

03:34.215 --> 03:35.881
right after we got engaged.

03:35.883 --> 03:38.217
He did something
that made me very uncomfortable.

03:38.219 --> 03:39.885
Did he make a pass at you?

03:39.887 --> 03:43.021
Marvin's brother Marlon
is always knocking at that door,

03:43.023 --> 03:44.823
trying to get some vitamin H.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.158
No. This is worse.

03:46.160 --> 03:48.660
He loaned me $200.

03:48.662 --> 03:50.162
(mug clanks)

03:50.164 --> 03:52.531
I couldn't afford
to buy Louis' wedding ring

03:52.533 --> 03:55.334
because I spent too much money
at the night market

03:55.336 --> 03:56.535
on some fake Jordache.

03:56.537 --> 03:57.869
Gene helped me out,

03:57.871 --> 04:00.205
and he's never let me
pay him back.

04:00.207 --> 04:01.707
And that's bad because...?

04:01.709 --> 04:03.242
In Chinese families,

04:03.244 --> 04:06.044
no one likes
to owe anyone anything.

04:06.046 --> 04:07.412
It's like how you must've felt

04:07.414 --> 04:09.181
when you kept my Tupperware
for too long.

04:09.183 --> 04:10.515
That's are actually
<i>my</i> Tupperware,

04:10.517 --> 04:12.017
and you still have it.

04:12.019 --> 04:14.519
And if you were Chinese,
I would feel bad about that.

04:15.522 --> 04:19.758
I've sent him checks for years,
but he never cashes them.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.593
If Gene
won't take your money directly,

04:21.595 --> 04:23.829
then just give him something
that's worth $200.

04:24.865 --> 04:27.633
Yeah. That's a good idea.

04:27.635 --> 04:29.201
Good news.

04:29.203 --> 04:31.270
Marlon booked a cruise,
just the three of us.

04:31.272 --> 04:32.738
He said bring your bikini!

04:32.740 --> 04:34.006
(chuckles)

04:35.542 --> 04:37.909
I mean...

04:37.911 --> 04:40.746
¶¶

04:40.748 --> 04:43.081
Hey, guys. What's wrong?

04:43.083 --> 04:44.716
We just saw "Bring the Pain,"

04:44.718 --> 04:47.085
and it's like a truth bomb
blew up in our faces.

04:47.087 --> 04:49.721
Chris Rock is right.
The war on drugs is a lie.

04:49.723 --> 04:51.089
Told you.

04:51.091 --> 04:53.258
"You know what
the good side of crack is?"

04:53.260 --> 04:55.594
No! I haven't seen it yet!
Let Chris tell me!

04:55.596 --> 04:57.329
Eddie, I thought you said
you'd watch it.

04:57.331 --> 04:58.630
I'm leaving for band camp soon.

04:58.632 --> 05:00.399
We only have
13 days of summer together!

05:00.401 --> 05:01.967
I will. I promise.

05:01.969 --> 05:04.336
Until then, let's just
talk about something else.

05:08.475 --> 05:10.309
Eddie... here's the thing.

05:10.311 --> 05:13.812
We all want Alison to say the
punch line to the crack joke.

05:13.814 --> 05:16.982
Alison wants to say the punch
line to the crack joke.

05:16.984 --> 05:20.452
So you can either stay or scoot.

05:20.454 --> 05:26.258
In five, four, three, two, one.

05:26.260 --> 05:31.029
(hip-hop music plays)

05:33.200 --> 05:35.233
(cheers and applause)

05:36.437 --> 05:38.637
(blows) Can't let you do that.

05:38.639 --> 05:40.872
Why?
You're not even watching TV!

05:40.874 --> 05:43.041
Mom told us to make sure
you stay honest.

05:43.043 --> 05:44.943
She made us deputy moms!

05:44.945 --> 05:46.378
Louis: Everyone get in the van.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.947
We have to go pick up
your Uncle Gene.

05:48.949 --> 05:53.852
¶¶

05:53.854 --> 05:56.388
Dad, I thought you didn't want
Uncle Gene to come visit.

05:56.390 --> 05:59.391
I don't, son, but I'm setting
an example for you boys.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.159
It's called being an adult.

06:01.161 --> 06:04.196
You have to do stuff you
don't want to do all the time.

06:04.198 --> 06:05.530
I'm glad Gene's coming.

06:08.702 --> 06:10.469
Gonna make him feel comfortable,

06:10.471 --> 06:14.206
treat him like a king...
for under $200.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.340
Gene: Hi, Louis.

06:15.342 --> 06:17.309
Gene!

06:17.311 --> 06:19.044
How did you... I came
from another gate.

06:19.046 --> 06:20.479
Ma!

06:20.481 --> 06:21.847
(both laugh)

06:21.849 --> 06:24.249
Mom, you look so small!

06:25.519 --> 06:27.419
(laughs) You look good, Gene.

06:27.421 --> 06:29.755
Nice to see you again.
Welcome to Orlando.

06:29.757 --> 06:32.190
"Welcome to Orlando."
Who are you, my parole officer?

06:32.192 --> 06:34.092
Come on. Bring it in!
(inhales deeply)

06:34.094 --> 06:36.695
Aww. (Chuckles)

06:36.697 --> 06:38.697
Oh, look at the three of you.

06:38.699 --> 06:40.265
Snap, Crackle, and Pop.

06:40.267 --> 06:42.100
Is that a joke
from 'Bring the Pain"?

06:42.102 --> 06:43.168
Let Chris tell me!

06:44.171 --> 06:45.337
You live in Taiwan.

06:45.339 --> 06:46.705
Why don't you have an accent?

06:46.707 --> 06:48.340
Well,
I work for Delta Airlines now,

06:48.342 --> 06:50.242
which is how I got
those last-minute tickets

06:50.244 --> 06:51.510
for nothing... (chuckles)

06:51.512 --> 06:52.611
Mm.

06:52.613 --> 06:54.212
And during pilot training,

06:54.214 --> 06:56.047
I had to learn
"Airline English".

06:56.049 --> 06:57.682
Prepare for an ocean landing.

06:57.684 --> 06:58.950
So cool!

06:58.952 --> 07:01.720
I want to be a flight attendant!

07:01.722 --> 07:03.355
Do you get to marry people
like ship captains?

07:03.357 --> 07:04.856
Nope, but I do it anyway.

07:04.858 --> 07:07.092
Well, I hope this pilot thing
works out for you.

07:07.094 --> 07:09.594
Unlike that lychee-nut
face cream you were developing.

07:09.596 --> 07:11.897
Wow. If I knew you were
having so much trouble,

07:11.899 --> 07:14.199
I would have brought some with me.
Trouble?

07:14.201 --> 07:16.368
Listen, Louis, I didn't
come here just to visit.

07:16.370 --> 07:18.503
I have some big news.

07:19.440 --> 07:20.472
I'm getting married.

07:20.474 --> 07:22.307
(gasps) Awesome!

07:22.309 --> 07:24.242
What better way to celebrate

07:24.244 --> 07:26.311
than by renting a Chevy Lumina
for two days?

07:26.313 --> 07:27.979
I'll pay for it.

07:27.981 --> 07:29.915
Oh, no, no, no, no.
Please, don't waste your money.

07:29.917 --> 07:31.917
Oh, you want
to play it that way?

07:31.919 --> 07:34.653
Okay. I can play it that way.

07:34.655 --> 07:35.887
I'm sorry. What?

07:35.889 --> 07:37.823
Congrats, Gene.
Who's the lucky lady?

07:37.825 --> 07:39.591
That masseuse you met in Phuket?

07:39.593 --> 07:40.659
(chuckles) No.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.427
Come on. It's her sister.

07:42.429 --> 07:43.829
Ah, I'm kidding!

07:43.831 --> 07:46.064
My fiancée's name is Margaret.

07:46.066 --> 07:47.399
She's a consultant.

07:47.401 --> 07:49.568
Very prominent family.

07:49.570 --> 07:51.470
Things are finally
coming together for me.

07:51.472 --> 07:53.572
(chuckles)
Oh, good for you, Gene.

07:53.574 --> 07:55.807
Uh, here, let me carry your bag.
No.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.075
I've got it.

07:57.077 --> 07:58.410
