Uh, hello, I'm Louis Huang.

09:35.509 --> 09:38.009
Welcome to Cattleman's Ranch!

09:38.011 --> 09:41.112
You know, I have
a very positive outlook on life.

09:41.114 --> 09:42.547
(Both laugh)

09:42.549 --> 09:45.116
I see that acting class
in Saipan paid off.

09:45.118 --> 09:46.618
(Normal voice) It did.
I'm still getting residuals

09:46.620 --> 09:48.386
from that
fabric-softener commercial.

09:48.388 --> 09:50.922
In fact, that's where I first
met my fiancée, Margaret.

09:50.924 --> 09:52.958
Man, I can't wait
for you all to meet her.

09:52.960 --> 09:54.292
You should see her ring.

09:54.294 --> 09:55.961
Oh, should we?
Should we see her ring?

09:55.963 --> 09:58.463
Well-done, Gene.

09:58.465 --> 09:59.965
Well-done.

09:59.967 --> 10:01.967
Is Jessica okay? I never know.

10:01.969 --> 10:03.802
All right.

10:03.804 --> 10:05.704
Anyway, Louis,
I didn't come all the way here

10:05.706 --> 10:06.972
just to announce my wedding.

10:06.974 --> 10:08.607
I know
we haven't seen each other

10:08.609 --> 10:12.310
since what happened at
the, you know, hot springs,

10:12.312 --> 10:14.946
but let's put the past behind us
and move forward.

10:14.948 --> 10:17.449
Look (sighs)
I want my future children

10:17.451 --> 10:19.084
to know their cousins.

10:19.086 --> 10:22.721
That's why I wanted to ask you,
in person...

10:22.723 --> 10:24.656
if you'd be my best man.

10:24.658 --> 10:26.725
¶¶

10:26.727 --> 10:28.627
(chuckles)

10:28.629 --> 10:30.829
I'd be honored.

10:30.831 --> 10:33.164
(chuckles) That's great!

10:33.166 --> 10:34.299
(chuckles)

10:34.301 --> 10:36.167
Come here, brother.

10:36.169 --> 10:37.268
Oh.

10:37.270 --> 10:39.337
