11:20.047 --> 11:21.212
(chuckling) No. No.

11:21.214 --> 11:23.381
No. No!

11:23.383 --> 11:25.216
No! No!!

11:25.218 --> 11:26.851
¶¶

11:26.853 --> 11:28.186
You still haven't seen it?

11:28.188 --> 11:30.388
But you and Alison
are running out of summer.

11:30.390 --> 11:33.358
My brothers will narc on me if I watch
it, and they're around all the time.

11:33.360 --> 11:36.828
Just do what I do when I want to
watch something R-rated or above.

11:36.830 --> 11:39.464
Videotape it late at night,
when everyone's asleep.

11:39.466 --> 11:42.801
Okay. Okay. Okay.

11:42.803 --> 11:44.969
That's how I saw
"Emmanuelle in Space."

11:44.971 --> 11:47.972
I wasn't ready for it.

11:47.974 --> 11:52.911
¶¶

11:53.980 --> 11:56.715
I'm sorry it's come to this.

11:56.717 --> 11:57.916
Keep the bag.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.684
What? No!

11:59.686 --> 12:01.686
I was gonna cut a hole
in your luggage

12:01.688 --> 12:05.056
where I could hide the $200 I
owe you for Louis' wedding ring

12:05.058 --> 12:07.358
so you wouldn't find it
till you got back to Taiwan.

12:07.360 --> 12:08.493
Oh, yeah. (Chuckles)

12:08.495 --> 12:10.095
I forgot about that.

12:10.097 --> 12:12.263
Look, I don't like to take money
from my sister-in-law,

12:12.265 --> 12:14.699
but if it means
that much to you, fine.

12:14.701 --> 12:16.000
You can pay me back.

12:16.002 --> 12:18.236
Really? Mm-hmm.

12:18.238 --> 12:20.004
(chuckles)

12:20.006 --> 12:21.573
Thank you.

12:21.575 --> 12:23.007
(chuckles) I can't believe

12:23.009 --> 12:24.943
you were gonna cut a hole
in my luggage.

12:24.945 --> 12:26.111
I mean, it's a Tumi.

12:26.113 --> 12:27.178
It says "Tami."

12:28.348 --> 12:30.014
Yeah, you got me. (Chuckles)

12:30.016 --> 12:32.417
(As Arnold Schwarzenegger)
No, it's not a Tumi.

12:32.419 --> 12:33.585
(laughs)

12:33.587 --> 12:35.186
It says "Tami."

12:36.256 --> 12:40.291
¶¶

12:41.561 --> 12:42.961
It worked!

12:42.963 --> 12:44.596
¶¶

12:44.598 --> 12:46.064
(sighs)

12:46.066 --> 12:48.266
Sorry I had to tape over you,
Bruce Leroy.

12:48.268 --> 12:50.201
¶¶

12:53.907 --> 12:55.306
What's up?!

12:55.308 --> 12:56.775
What's up, Chris Rock?

12:57.444 --> 12:59.277
Unh, unh, unh.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.646
What the hell?! Eddie,
don't say "hell."

13:01.648 --> 13:03.281
We knew
you'd try something like this,

13:03.283 --> 13:04.983
so we used Dad's camcorder

13:04.985 --> 13:06.684
to record over
your Chris Rock tape.

13:07.621 --> 13:09.821
Thank you, Eddie. We take
that word as a compliment.

13:09.823 --> 13:11.556
I didn't say anything.

13:11.558 --> 13:13.424
I thought you'd call us nerds.

13:13.426 --> 13:15.960
We recorded
a more age-appropriate program

13:15.962 --> 13:17.228
for you to watch.

13:17.230 --> 13:18.730
("Bless My Happy Home" plays)

13:20.934 --> 13:23.668
(laughs) Those hayseeds!

13:23.670 --> 13:25.003
(chuckles)

13:27.507 --> 13:29.340
What is that on your face?

13:29.342 --> 13:31.810
Just, uh, shining up the lobby.

13:31.812 --> 13:33.311
(chuckles)

13:37.017 --> 13:39.083
What's that on<i> your</i> face?

13:39.085 --> 13:41.252
What? You're smiling.

13:41.254 --> 13:43.888
I am. I am happy.

13:44.925 --> 13:47.158
I can't just be happy
for no reason?

13:47.160 --> 13:49.594
We both know you can't.
What's going on?

13:49.596 --> 13:51.863
(sighs) Okay. Fine.

13:51.865 --> 13:53.031
I never told you this.

13:53.033 --> 13:54.766
A long time ago,

13:54.768 --> 13:57.302
I borrowed money from Gene
to buy your wedding ring...

13:57.304 --> 13:59.037
What?! ...and I've been trying

13:59.039 --> 14:01.539
for all these years to pay him
back, and he never let me.

14:01.541 --> 14:04.542
And today, I finally succeeded.

14:04.544 --> 14:06.010
You shouldn't have done that.

14:06.012 --> 14:07.712
I know, but we were in Taiwan,

14:07.714 --> 14:09.848
and Jordache had just come out
with their Basics line.

14:09.850 --> 14:11.683
They had horse-face rivets
down the leg.

14:11.685 --> 14:13.718
No, you shouldn't have
paid him back.

14:13.720 --> 14:14.853
He owes us thousands.

14:14.855 --> 14:16.020
Wait.

14:16.022 --> 14:18.723
<i>He</i> owes<i> us</i> money?

14:18.725 --> 14:21.125
I've been sending him money
for years.

14:21.127 --> 14:22.493
Why? He's my brother.

14:22.495 --> 14:24.796
It's my responsibility
to help him.

14:24.798 --> 14:31.302
So, he owes us thousands
and he let me give him $200?!

14:31.304 --> 14:34.072
(ragtime music playing on piano)

14:34.074 --> 14:36.140
(crash, sour notes play)

14:37.878 --> 14:40.044
You broke the piano?!

14:40.046 --> 14:41.880
I wanted to play some ragtime
before bed.

14:41.882 --> 14:43.648
You know how
I like to pound the keys.

14:48.722 --> 14:51.890
At least you're doing well now,
so you can pay for this.

14:51.892 --> 14:53.091
(inhales sharply)

14:53.093 --> 14:54.726
Yeah, I got a wedding coming up,

14:54.728 --> 14:56.928
and, like, Margaret wants
to release doves, so...

14:56.930 --> 14:59.364
Well, you can use the $200
I just gave you.

14:59.366 --> 15:01.532
Or maybe
you have something left over

15:01.534 --> 15:04.035
from the money I sent you
for piano lessons,

15:04.037 --> 15:06.504
acting classes, flight school,

15:06.506 --> 15:09.340
lychee-nut farming,
vacuum-repair workshop...

15:09.342 --> 15:11.776
Don't pretend to be
this generous guy.

15:11.778 --> 15:14.679
You sent me that money
because you felt guilty

15:14.681 --> 15:17.181
about what happened
at the hot springs.

15:17.183 --> 15:20.685
You haven't changed. You're still not
over what happened at the hot springs.

15:20.687 --> 15:22.687
Damn right I'm not!
I'll<i> never</i> be over it!

15:22.689 --> 15:24.923
You stole America from me!

15:24.925 --> 15:28.159
(whirring)

15:29.896 --> 15:32.630
Is the VCR recording something?

15:32.632 --> 15:34.699
It's a head cleaner.
I'm cleaning the heads.

15:34.701 --> 15:36.935
I care about our things.

15:36.937 --> 15:38.269
¶¶

15:43.109 --> 15:44.742
What are you talking about?

15:44.744 --> 15:47.211
What do you mean,
Louis stole America from you?

15:47.213 --> 15:50.148
Get over it, Gene.
It was a long time ago.

15:50.150 --> 15:51.716
Oh, Louis never told you about

15:51.718 --> 15:53.318
what happened
at the hot springs?

15:53.320 --> 15:55.253
You mean the time
he wore a bathing suit

15:55.255 --> 15:57.555
and everyone made fun of him
for not being naked?

15:57.557 --> 15:58.923
(scoffs) Please.

15:58.925 --> 16:01.092
Louis was the first one
to strip nude.

16:01.094 --> 16:02.160
He<i> arrived</i> nude.

16:02.162 --> 16:04.495
I'm proud of my body.

16:04.497 --> 16:06.497
So, what<i> really</i> happened?

16:22.015 --> 16:23.081
(chuckles)

16:40.600 --> 16:42.500
Okay. Yes. I'll go.

16:43.603 --> 16:45.169
Louis: Say bye to Mom for me!

16:49.876 --> 16:51.342
You said yes?

16:51.344 --> 16:53.544
In the middle
of a Chinese polite fight?!

16:53.546 --> 16:55.680
Gene: That was
so selfish of you.

16:55.682 --> 16:57.048
You should have sacrificed.

16:57.050 --> 16:58.216
I<i> did</i> sacrifice!

16:58.218 --> 16:59.884
I took on the responsibility

16:59.886 --> 17:02.020
of being the one
who got to come here.

17:02.022 --> 17:04.288
I worked hard, got a job,
sent money back,

17:04.290 --> 17:06.557
not just to you,
but to the whole family.

17:06.559 --> 17:09.127
Would you have done that?
I don't know.

17:09.129 --> 17:10.962
I never got the opportunity.
<i>You</i> did.

17:10.964 --> 17:14.132
You took my coming to America
as an excuse to not succeed.

17:14.134 --> 17:16.968
That's why it took you so long
to get it together.

17:16.970 --> 17:18.636
But you have a great job now!

17:18.638 --> 17:20.171
You're about to get married.

17:20.173 --> 17:21.506
Your life turned out fine.

17:21.508 --> 17:22.874
Eventually, it did!

17:22.876 --> 17:25.943
But who knows
what my life could have become?!

17:28.181 --> 17:32.250
Maybe we would have sat next to
<i>my</i> mullet at the restaurant.

17:32.252 --> 17:34.585
¶¶

17:34.587 --> 17:36.054
(door closes)

17:36.056 --> 17:37.422
¶¶

17:38.892 --> 17:39.891
(door closes)

17:39.893 --> 17:41.492
Eddie: We need to talk.

17:41.494 --> 17:43.995
Free HBO is almost over,
and Alison's leaving in 11 days.

17:43.997 --> 17:47.031
So I came in to tell you
that I give up.

17:47.033 --> 17:50.835
But also to ask you...
to join me.

17:50.837 --> 17:52.937
You're just saying that 'cause
you want to watch your show.

17:52.939 --> 17:54.672
True, true.

17:54.674 --> 17:57.008
But... I also don't want
to be like Dad and Uncle Gene.

17:57.010 --> 17:59.510
I don't want this
to be our hot springs.

17:59.512 --> 18:01.345
I have no idea what that means.

18:01.347 --> 18:03.915
We're brothers.
We're all each other has.

18:03.917 --> 18:06.250
Mom divided us,
but let's come together...

18:06.252 --> 18:08.352
like Voltron.

18:09.189 --> 18:10.388
I'm the leg!

18:10.390 --> 18:13.291
¶¶

18:13.293 --> 18:15.093
Do you want to talk about it?

18:15.095 --> 18:17.128
No. I've done
enough talking today.

18:17.130 --> 18:19.764
Okay. Good night.

18:21.267 --> 18:25.837
(mumbling)

18:27.574 --> 18:29.307
Louis, stop mumbling.

18:29.309 --> 18:30.808
Say words or don't say words.

18:30.810 --> 18:31.876
I feel bad.

18:31.878 --> 18:34.045
And what if Gene's right?

18:34.047 --> 18:35.379
(sighs)

18:35.381 --> 18:38.950
You have nothing
to feel bad about.

18:38.952 --> 18:41.419
But his life would probably
be better if he came here.

18:41.421 --> 18:43.054
You don't know that!

18:43.056 --> 18:45.389
Besides, only one of you
was gonna get the opportunity.

18:45.391 --> 18:47.291
Why shouldn't it be you?

18:47.293 --> 18:48.726
I guess...

18:48.728 --> 18:50.828
If you hadn't come here,
we never would have met.

18:51.831 --> 18:54.832
I don't regret
the decision you made.

18:54.834 --> 18:57.668
You have nothing
to apologize for.

18:57.670 --> 18:59.937
Thank you.

18:59.939 --> 19:03.674
Unless you want to set
a good example for the boys.

19:03.676 --> 19:06.310
(groans) I hate being an adult.

19:06.312 --> 19:08.679
Me, too.

19:08.681 --> 19:11.315
I'm lying. I love it.

19:11.317 --> 19:14.418
I love every aspect of it.

19:14.420 --> 19:15.586
(sighs)

19:15.588 --> 19:17.021
Ma, have you seen Gene?

19:17.023 --> 19:19.190
I can't find him.

19:19.192 --> 19:22.193
¶¶

19:25.031 --> 19:27.098
You better recognize!

19:27.100 --> 19:28.366
(laughter)

19:28.368 --> 19:29.700
Shh!

19:29.702 --> 19:32.103
Don't laugh so loud.
You'll wake Mom and Dad.

19:32.105 --> 19:33.738
Just snap instead of laugh.

19:36.042 --> 19:38.209
I don't care for
all the bad language,

19:38.211 --> 19:40.811
but this is just as educational
as "Square One."

19:40.813 --> 19:43.514
I'm just glad
he doesn't do lame Asian jokes.

19:43.516 --> 19:45.283
I don't care what time it is.

19:45.285 --> 19:46.617
I'm calling Alison now.

19:49.322 --> 19:50.621
We still h...

19:52.725 --> 19:54.792
I need to call the airline.

19:54.794 --> 19:56.127
What's going on?

19:56.129 --> 19:57.662
Gene went back to Taiwan.

19:57.664 --> 20:00.231
He left this note
uninviting us to the wedding.

20:00.233 --> 20:02.133
(gasps) And he took Grandma.

20:02.135 --> 20:04.535
(gasps) Forever?

20:04.537 --> 20:05.870
No! Just for the wedding.

20:06.906 --> 20:08.806
So, why do you need
to call the airline?

20:08.808 --> 20:11.409
Because I need to make
things right with my brother.

20:11.411 --> 20:12.543
(sighs)

20:12.545 --> 20:13.878
We're all going to Taiwan.

20:13.880 --> 20:15.046
(chuckles)

20:15.048 --> 20:16.047
Good.

20:16.049 --> 20:18.516
I'm gonna get my $200 back.

20:18.518 --> 20:20.318
Turn off the race riot
and start packing.

20:24.824 --> 20:26.324
You're going to Taiwan?!

20:26.326 --> 20:27.692
But I leave for band camp in 10 days!
It's okay.

20:27.694 --> 20:28.859
I'm gonna get myself
a phone card,

20:28.861 --> 20:31.095
and I'll call you every day.

20:31.097 --> 20:32.730
I'll even try to fax you
when possible.

20:32.732 --> 20:34.865
But you're gonna need
to set up an account at Kinko's.

20:34.867 --> 20:36.867
There's one
right by my dad's work.

20:36.869 --> 20:38.336
And when I get back,

20:38.338 --> 20:40.071
you and I will still have
half a day together,

20:40.073 --> 20:41.939
and we'll spend our summer
talking about Chris Rock then.

20:41.941 --> 20:44.442
(scraping)

